Writes the specified data followed by a newline to the standard output stream.

```csharp
Console.WriteLine("Hello, World!");
Console.WriteLine($"Value: {x}");
Console.WriteLine("{0} + {1} = {2}", a, b, a+b);
```

Writes the specified data to the standard output stream without a trailing newline.

```csharp
Console.Write("Enter name: ");
Console.Write($"{item}, ");
```

Reads the next line of characters from the standard input stream.

```csharp
string? input = Console.ReadLine();
var name = Console.ReadLine() ?? "";
```

Obtains the next character or function key pressed by the user.

```csharp
ConsoleKeyInfo key = Console.ReadKey();
Console.ReadKey(intercept: true); // don't display
if (key.Key == ConsoleKey.Enter) { }
```

Writes a message followed by a line terminator to the trace listeners in the Listeners collection.

```csharp
Debug.WriteLine("Entering method");
Debug.WriteLine($"Value: {x}");
```

Declares a reference type that supports inheritance, polymorphism, and encapsulation.

```csharp
public class MyClass
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public void DoWork() { }
}
```

Declares a value type that can encapsulate data and related functionality.

```csharp
public struct Point
{
    public double X { get; set; }
    public double Y { get; set; }
}
```

Declares a reference type with value-based equality, immutability support, and concise syntax.

```csharp
public record Person(string Name, int Age);
public record class Employee(string Name, string Department);
public record struct Point(double X, double Y);
```

Declares an interface that defines a contract for classes and structs.

```csharp
public interface IRepository<T>
{
    T GetById(int id);
    IEnumerable<T> GetAll();
    void Add(T entity);
}
```

Declares a scope for organizing code and controlling type visibility.

```csharp
namespace MyApp.Models
{
    public class User { }
}
```

Declares a namespace that applies to the entire file without nesting braces.

```csharp
namespace MyApp.Models;

public class User { }
public class Role { }
```

Imports types from a namespace or creates a type alias.

```csharp
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using static System.Math;
using Alias = System.Collections.Generic.List<int>;
```

Applies a using directive to every source file in the project.

```csharp
global using System;
global using System.Collections.Generic;
global using static System.Math;
```

Marks a method as asynchronous and awaits the completion of tasks.

```csharp
public async Task<string> FetchDataAsync()
{
    var result = await httpClient.GetStringAsync(url);
    return result;
}
```

Lets the compiler determine the type from the initializer expression.

```csharp
var name = "Alice";
var numbers = new List<int> { 1, 2, 3 };
var result = await GetDataAsync();
```

Creates a new instance of a type. Supports target-typed new expressions (C# 9+).

```csharp
var list = new List<int>();
Person p = new("Alice", 30);
var dict = new Dictionary<string, int>();
```

Returns each element one at a time from an iterator method.

```csharp
public IEnumerable<int> GetNumbers()
{
    yield return 1;
    yield return 2;
    yield return 3;
}
```

Signals the end of iteration in an iterator method.

```csharp
public IEnumerable<int> GetPositive(IEnumerable<int> items)
{
    foreach (var item in items)
    {
        if (item < 0) yield break;
        yield return item;
    }
}
```

Indicates that a property or field must be set during object initialization.

```csharp
public class Person
{
    public required string Name { get; init; }
    public required int Age { get; init; }
}
var p = new Person { Name = "Alice", Age = 30 };
```

Defines an init-only setter that can only be called during object construction or initialization.

```csharp
public class Config
{
    public string Name { get; init; }
    public int Value { get; init; }
}
var c = new Config { Name = "test", Value = 42 };
```

Declares a class that cannot be instantiated directly and may contain abstract members.

```csharp
public abstract class Shape
{
    public abstract double Area();
    public virtual void Draw() { }
}
```

Replaces format items in a string with the string representations of corresponding objects.

```csharp
string s = string.Format("{0} is {1} years old", name, age);
string s2 = string.Format("{0:C2}", price);
string s3 = string.Format("{0:D4}", id);
```

Concatenates the elements of a collection, using the specified separator between each element.

```csharp
string csv = string.Join(", ", names);
string path = string.Join("/", segments);
string line = string.Join("\t", values);
```

Indicates whether the specified string is null or an empty string ("").

```csharp
if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(input))
    return default;
```

Indicates whether a specified string is null, empty, or consists only of white-space characters.

```csharp
if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(input))
    throw new ArgumentException("Input required");
```

Concatenates one or more instances of String, or the String representations of the values of one or more objects.

```csharp
string result = string.Concat("Hello", " ", "World");
string all = string.Concat(names);
```

Compares two specified String objects and returns an integer that indicates their relative position in the sort order.

```csharp
int cmp = string.Compare(a, b, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
if (string.Compare(s1, s2) == 0) { }
```

Creates a formatted string using embedded expressions prefixed with $.

```csharp
string msg = $"Hello, {name}!";
string info = $"{item.Name}: {item.Price:C2}";
string raw = $"""Value is {value}""";
```

Retrieves a substring from this instance.

```csharp
string sub = text.Substring(0, 5);
string rest = text.Substring(3);
```

Returns a value indicating whether a specified substring occurs within this string.

```csharp
bool found = text.Contains("search");
bool ci = text.Contains("SEARCH", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
```

Returns a new string in which all occurrences of a specified string are replaced.

```csharp
string result = text.Replace("old", "new");
string clean = input.Replace("\n", " ");
```

Splits a string into substrings based on specified delimiters.

```csharp
string[] words = text.Split(' ');
string[] parts = csv.Split(',', StringSplitOptions.TrimEntries);
string[] lines = text.Split('\n');
```

Represents a strongly typed list of objects that can be accessed by index.

```csharp
var list = new List<string> { "a", "b", "c" };
list.Add("d");
list.Remove("b");
int count = list.Count;
```

Initializes a new instance of the List<T> class.

```csharp
var items = new List<string>();
var numbers = new List<int> { 1, 2, 3 };
var sized = new List<double>(capacity: 100);
```

Represents a collection of key/value pairs with fast key lookups.

```csharp
var dict = new Dictionary<string, int>
{
    ["alice"] = 1,
    ["bob"] = 2
};
dict.TryGetValue("alice", out int val);
```

Initializes a new instance of the Dictionary<TKey,TValue> class.

```csharp
var map = new Dictionary<string, int>();
var lookup = new Dictionary<int, string>(capacity: 50);
```

Represents a set of values with O(1) lookups and no duplicates.

```csharp
var set = new HashSet<string> { "a", "b", "c" };
set.Add("d");
bool exists = set.Contains("a");
set.UnionWith(otherSet);
```

Represents a first-in, first-out (FIFO) collection of objects.

```csharp
var queue = new Queue<string>();
queue.Enqueue("first");
string next = queue.Dequeue();
string peek = queue.Peek();
```

Represents a last-in, first-out (LIFO) collection of objects.

```csharp
var stack = new Stack<int>();
stack.Push(1);
int top = stack.Pop();
int peek = stack.Peek();
```

Filters a sequence of values based on a predicate.

```csharp
var adults = people.Where(p => p.Age >= 18);
var evens = numbers.Where(n => n % 2 == 0);
var active = items.Where(i => i.IsActive);
```

Projects each element of a sequence into a new form.

```csharp
var names = people.Select(p => p.Name);
var dtos = items.Select(i => new ItemDto(i.Id, i.Name));
var indexed = list.Select((item, i) => $"{i}: {item}");
```

Projects each element to a sequence and flattens the resulting sequences into one.

```csharp
var allOrders = customers.SelectMany(c => c.Orders);
var chars = words.SelectMany(w => w.ToCharArray());
```

Sorts the elements of a sequence in ascending order according to a key.

```csharp
var sorted = people.OrderBy(p => p.Name);
var byAge = people.OrderBy(p => p.Age).ThenBy(p => p.Name);
```

Sorts the elements of a sequence in descending order according to a key.

```csharp
var newest = items.OrderByDescending(i => i.CreatedAt);
var topScores = scores.OrderByDescending(s => s);
```

Groups the elements of a sequence according to a specified key selector function.

```csharp
var groups = people.GroupBy(p => p.Department);
foreach (var g in groups)
    Console.WriteLine($"{g.Key}: {g.Count()}");
```

Returns the first element of a sequence. Throws InvalidOperationException if no elements.

```csharp
var first = items.First();
var match = items.First(x => x.IsValid);
```

Returns the first element, or a default value if no element is found.

```csharp
var item = items.FirstOrDefault();
var match = items.FirstOrDefault(x => x.Id == id);
var safe = items.FirstOrDefault(x => x.Id == id, fallback);
```

Returns the only element of a sequence. Throws if there is not exactly one element.

```csharp
var only = items.Single();
var match = items.Single(x => x.Id == id);
```

Determines whether any element of a sequence satisfies a condition.

```csharp
bool hasItems = list.Any();
bool hasAdults = people.Any(p => p.Age >= 18);
```

Determines whether all elements of a sequence satisfy a condition.

```csharp
bool allValid = items.All(i => i.IsValid);
bool allPositive = numbers.All(n => n > 0);
```

Returns the number of elements in a sequence, optionally filtered by a predicate.

```csharp
int total = items.Count();
int active = items.Count(i => i.IsActive);
```

Computes the sum of a sequence of numeric values.

```csharp
int total = numbers.Sum();
decimal revenue = orders.Sum(o => o.Amount);
```

Computes the average of a sequence of numeric values.

```csharp
double avg = scores.Average();
double avgAge = people.Average(p => p.Age);
```

Returns the minimum value in a sequence.

```csharp
int min = numbers.Min();
DateTime earliest = events.Min(e => e.Date);
```

Returns the maximum value in a sequence.

```csharp
int max = numbers.Max();
decimal highest = products.Max(p => p.Price);
```

Applies an accumulator function over a sequence.

```csharp
int product = numbers.Aggregate((a, b) => a * b);
string sentence = words.Aggregate((a, b) => $"{a} {b}");
int sum = numbers.Aggregate(0, (acc, n) => acc + n);
```

Returns distinct elements from a sequence.

```csharp
var unique = numbers.Distinct();
var uniqueNames = people.Select(p => p.Name).Distinct();
```

Returns a specified number of contiguous elements from the start of a sequence.

```csharp
var top5 = items.Take(5);
var page = items.Skip(20).Take(10);
var range = items.Take(3..7);
```

Bypasses a specified number of elements in a sequence and returns the remaining elements.

```csharp
var rest = items.Skip(5);
var page2 = items.Skip(10).Take(10);
```

Creates a List<T> from an IEnumerable<T>.

```csharp
var list = query.ToList();
var names = people.Select(p => p.Name).ToList();
```

Creates an array from an IEnumerable<T>.

```csharp
int[] arr = numbers.ToArray();
string[] names = people.Select(p => p.Name).ToArray();
```

Creates a Dictionary<TKey,TValue> from an IEnumerable<T>.

```csharp
var dict = people.ToDictionary(p => p.Id, p => p.Name);
var lookup = items.ToDictionary(i => i.Key);
```

Concatenates two sequences.

```csharp
var all = first.Concat(second);
var combined = list1.Concat(list2).ToList();
```

Produces a sequence of tuples from two sequences element-by-element.

```csharp
var pairs = names.Zip(scores);
var results = names.Zip(scores, (n, s) => $"{n}: {s}");
```

Queues the specified work to run on the ThreadPool and returns a Task representing that work.

```csharp
await Task.Run(() => HeavyComputation());
var result = await Task.Run(() => Calculate(x));
```

Creates a task that will complete when all of the supplied tasks have completed.

```csharp
await Task.WhenAll(task1, task2, task3);
var results = await Task.WhenAll(tasks);
```

Creates a task that completes when any of the supplied tasks have completed.

```csharp
var completed = await Task.WhenAny(task1, task2);
if (completed == task1) { }
```

Creates a Task<TResult> that is completed with the specified result.

```csharp
return Task.FromResult(42);
return Task.FromResult<string?>(null);
```

Declares an asynchronous method that returns a Task.

```csharp
public async Task DoWorkAsync()
{
    await Task.Delay(100);
}

public async Task<int> GetValueAsync()
{
    return await FetchAsync();
}
```

Returns the larger of two specified numbers.

```csharp
int bigger = Math.Max(a, b);
double max = Math.Max(3.14, 2.72);
```

Returns the smaller of two specified numbers.

```csharp
int smaller = Math.Min(a, b);
double min = Math.Min(x, y);
```

Converts the string representation of a number to its 32-bit signed integer equivalent.

```csharp
int n = int.Parse("42");
int hex = int.Parse("FF", NumberStyles.HexNumber);
```

Tries to convert the string representation of a number to its integer equivalent. Returns whether the conversion succeeded.

```csharp
if (int.TryParse(input, out int result))
    Console.WriteLine(result);
```

Initializes a new instance of the Guid structure with a unique value.

```csharp
Guid id = Guid.NewGuid();
string idStr = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
```

Gets a DateTime object set to the current date and time on this computer, expressed as the local time.

```csharp
DateTime now = DateTime.Now;
string formatted = DateTime.Now.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd");
```

Gets a DateTime object set to the current date and time expressed as Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

```csharp
DateTime utc = DateTime.UtcNow;
long timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow.Ticks;
```

Returns a TimeSpan that represents a specified number of seconds.

```csharp
var ts = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(30);
var delay = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(2.5);
```

Returns an empty IEnumerable<T> that has the specified type argument.

```csharp
IEnumerable<string> empty = Enumerable.Empty<string>();
return items ?? Enumerable.Empty<Item>();
```

Generates a sequence that contains one repeated value.

```csharp
var zeros = Enumerable.Repeat(0, 10);
var stars = Enumerable.Repeat("*", 5);
```

Tests an expression against a pattern using the is keyword.

```csharp
if (obj is string s)
    Console.WriteLine(s.Length);
if (result is not null)
    Process(result);
if (value is >= 0 and <= 100)
    Console.WriteLine("In range");
```

Evaluates an expression against a set of patterns and returns the matching result.

```csharp
var result = status switch
{
    Status.Active => "Active",
    Status.Inactive => "Inactive",
    _ => "Unknown"
};

var msg = obj switch
{
    int n => $"int: {n}",
    string s => $"string: {s}",
    null => "null",
    _ => "other"
};
```

Adds a condition guard to a pattern in a switch or catch clause.

```csharp
var desc = value switch
{
    int n when n > 0 => "positive",
    int n when n < 0 => "negative",
    _ => "zero"
};

catch (Exception ex) when (ex.Message.Contains("timeout"))
{
    Retry();
}
```

Matches objects by their property values in a pattern.

```csharp
if (person is { Name: "Alice", Age: >= 18 })
    Console.WriteLine("Adult Alice");

var result = shape switch
{
    { Area: > 100 } => "large",
    { Area: > 0 } => "small",
    _ => "none"
};
```
